Bertox</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/undaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ndaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/01 2:49:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Caster loot **** SUCKS!!! &gt;:{</span><hr size=1> Yes Slibus, that is exactly the problem... but why can't casters get gear that will greatly increase their usefulness? Several times I've had to fight naked, with a few borrowed malachite, and I do just ducky, thank you very much. My mage has crap gear and it doesn't make any difference. <br>
<br>
But why is it OK to have tunics to regen HP, and no similar mana regen items? Why are there melee haste items all over the place, and nothing to shorten casting time? Why is there plenty of STR gear to increase melee damage, but nothing to increase spell damage? Why are there buffs to make melee MUCH more effective, and nothing that makes casters more effective, just buffs to increase our mana pool? We will still get resisted by blue mobs, no matter how many buffs we sport.<br>
<br>
I'm not angry about it =) I'm just wondering why VI chose to set the game up in this way. I don't think they are intentionally slighting casters. Why would they do that? I'm just really happy I chose to be a mage. Give me a bag full of malachite and i'm good to go! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/01 3:06:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Caster loot **** SUCKS!!! &gt;:{</span><hr size=1> Yeah, on the one hand it is great to be able to handle any fight with just a handful of Malichites.  It really points out how little gear actually helps us casters.  <br>
<br>
I don't have very good gear as a level 51 Mage...and I don't really care all that much.   The only items I have found to be useful, in order of need, are:<br>
<br>
- Malichite<br>
- Focus Items (now I need to get the Mastery Staffs)<br>
- AC gear<br>
- Int gear (for a larger mana pool, really only useful in emergencies)<br>
- Resist gear.<br>
<br>
Forget items that reduce casting time, that would cause a balance nightmere.   Imagine an Enchanter that could reduce cast time on Mez, Stun, etc, by 50%.  Forget it.<br>
<br>
Mana regen increase is the *only* reasonable thing that will increase out damage output and effectiveness.  I think mana regen items should be available as frequently as melee Haste items.  Why cannot the Robe of Elements, O-robe, or some mid 30's type robe have a mana regen effect like breeze?   Apothic belt could get C1 regen speed?   Make these stack with Enchanter and Bard effects?<br>
<br>
This would address some of the damage balance issue that we are seeing post 55+, as melee types can dish out damage faster then we can via our mana regen rate and casting DDs (that can get resisted). <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
Mage 51st Season, Spec-Evocation, Xegony<br>
Proud member of "The Ring of Truth"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaamilae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aamilae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/01 4:29:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://presys.com/~thepub/images/aamilae_boardprofile.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Caster loot **** SUCKS!!! &gt;:{</span><hr size=1> Think of it this way..  a melee's improved gear is directly comparable to a caster gaining levels and getting new spells.  For me I have become more versatile and more useful to my guild and others as I have gained levels (less resists) and aquired all of my spells.  A single level 60 mage can debuff mobs in ToV to the point where they can be slowed with an added tash, they can do that naked too.  You would be hard pressed to find a single level 60 warrior capable of effectively tanking any post 60 mob naked, it just won't happen.<br>
<br>
